In elicitation, the modal future was also accepted in interrogatives when asking the hearer to make a promise, as in (\ref{exCommissiveQuestionElicitation}), the interrogative counterpart to (\ref{exCommissiveFelbergstory}) above. In compliance with its semantics of a settled future, it was considered infeliticious when asking for a prediction (\ref{exCommissiveQuestionElicitationPrediction}).

